agentData.mission: Perform a targeted, comprehensive literature and resource search across the specified mathematical domains (algebra, calculus, geometry, probability, statistics, discrete math, and mathematical modeling). For each domain, collect seminal papers, canonical textbooks, recent survey articles, key theorems, representative worked examples (with references to proofs), and any publicly available datasets or simulation examples; produce an annotated bibliography with direct links and short notes on why each item is important.
